statements: SELECT * FROM correlation_coefficients;
SELECT feature1, correlation_coefficient FROM correlation_coefficients WHERE feature2 = 'example';
SELECT correlation_coefficient, feature2 FROM correlation_coefficients ORDER BY correlation_coefficient DESC;
SELECT DISTINCT feature1 FROM correlation_coefficients;
SELECT feature1, feature2, correlation_coefficient FROM correlation_coefficients WHERE feature1 <> feature2;
SELECT feature1, feature2, correlation_coefficient FROM correlation_coefficients WHERE correlation_coefficient > 0.8 ORDER BY feature1 ASC, correlation_coefficient DESC LIMIT 10;
SELECT * FROM correlation_coefficients WHERE feature1 LIKE 'A%' OR feature2 LIKE '%B' ORDER BY feature1 DESC, feature2 ASC;
SELECT DISTINCT feature1 FROM correlation_coefficients WHERE correlation_coefficient < 0.5;
SELECT feature1, AVG(correlation_coefficient) AS avg_correlation FROM correlation_coefficients GROUP BY feature1 HAVING AVG(correlation_coefficient) > 0.4 ORDER BY avg_correlation DESC;
SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_correlations, MAX(correlation_coefficient) AS max_correlation FROM correlation_coefficients;
